                        </para>
			                  </info>
                  </external.link>
               </subordinate>.
		 Convergence questions related to infinite series were largely dealt with at an intuitive level. The development of a rigorous approach to convergence questions is the work of mathematicians in the 19th century, with main contributors 
		<subordinate>
                  <hot>Carl Friedrich Gauß</hot>
                  <external.link href="http://webmath.facsci.ualberta.ca:8080/cocoon/fcm/Content/ExternalSources/Gauss_CarlFriedrich/GaussCarl.xml"
